=== Events ===
* In {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治}} 27th Year (1894 AD) – The {{ill|Kōgo Peasant War|ja|甲午農民戦争}} (also known as the Tōgakutō Rebellion) occurred.

== Months of Kōgo ==
In a {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (i.e. when the Ten Heavenly Stems are {{ill|Xin|ja|辛}} or {{ill|Bing|ja|丙}}), the month of {{ill|May|ja|5月}} becomes the {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month}} of Kōgo. However, here the term “month” may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} or to a seasonal month (from {{ill|Mangzhong|ja|芒種}} until the day before {{ill|Xiaoshu|ja|小暑}}) as applicable.

== Days of Kōgo ==
The {{ill|Day Selection|ja|選日|1=Senjitsu}} for a Kōgo day is as follows.
=== Day Selection ===
A Kōgo day is the 2nd day of {{ill|Ten Heaven, One Heaven|ja|天一天上}}.

