{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}

'''Yang Wood Horse also known as 甲午''' (kinoeuma, kōbokunouma, kougo) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支}}.

It is the 31st combination of the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding combination is {{ill|Guisi|ja|癸巳}} and the following combination is {{ill|Otsuji|ja|乙未}}. In the system of {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}}’ {{ill|Jia|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木}}, while the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}}’ {{ill|Horse|ja|午|1=Horse (zodiac)|lt=Horse (午)}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, and they interact by {{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}} (Wood produces Fire).

